The paper deals with untangling planar graphs and polygons, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithm presented in the paper involves moving vertices in a graph, which is a common operation in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses upper bounds on the number of fixed vertices in untangling graphs, which is related to combinatorics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper mentions the use of the algorithm in practical applications such as circuit design, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
